<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="341" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1436,1605,1667]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1605,1631]" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Remarks.</emphasis>
The generic classification of pterygometopids is not yet in a stable state. The species described below is placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zhou, Yuan &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="1998" box="[260,365,1641,1667]" class="Trilobita" family="Pterygometopidae" genus="Yanhaoia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phacopida" pageId="40" pageNumber="341" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[260,365,1641,1667]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="341">Yanhaoia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of its unusually large eyes combined with a relatively narrow axis.
</paragraph>
